<subSubSection id="C30108F90AF846852CFCFB29FA92D24D" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA45B720AF846852CFCFB29FA92D24D" blockId="215.[151,1437,1191,2010]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852CFCFB29FEF2D385" bold="true" box="[151,313,1191,1218]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Introduction:</emphasis>
the species in this subfamily are only known from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852FECFB26FBECD385" authorityName="R.Brown" authorityYear="1810" box="[903,1063,1192,1218]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Combretaceae</taxonomicName>
and the mistletoe families Loranathaceae and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852D55FB42FE65D3A1" box="[318,430,1228,1254]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Viscaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Viscaceae</taxonomicName>
in southern Africa. It includes two genera, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852FF6FB42FB09D3A1" authority="McConnel" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[925,1218,1228,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852FF6FB42FB8FD3A1" box="[925,1092,1228,1254]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Rhodesaclerda</emphasis>
McConnel
</taxonomicName>
with 3 species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852CFCFB7EFDDDD24D" authority="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[151,534,1264,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Kwazulaclerda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852CFCFB7EFE8BD24D" box="[151,320,1264,1290]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Kwazulaclerda</emphasis>
Hodgson &amp; Millar
</taxonomicName>
with 1 species. This group was last revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A26830AF84685284EFB7EFA92D24D" author="Hodgson and Millar" box="[1061,1369,1264,1290]" firstAuthor="Hodgson" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" pagination="469 - 517" refId="ref204361" refString="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; Millar, I. M. (2002) A new subfamily, two new genera and three new species of Aclerdidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) from southern Africa, with a phylogenetic analysis of relationships. Systematic Entomology, 27 (4), 469 - 517. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1365 - 3113.2002.00189. x" type="journal article" year="2002">Hodgson and Millar (2002)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30108F90AF8468B2CACFA9DFE04D55C" lastPageId="217" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA45B720AF8468B2CACFA9DFE04D55C" blockId="215.[151,1437,1191,2010]" lastBlockId="217.[151,1437,153,756]" lastPageId="217" lastPageNumber="218" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852CACFA9DFC91D269" bold="true" box="[199,858,1299,1326]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Subfamily diagnosis based on adult male morphology</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="132047F70AF846852F07FA9AFC0FD269" box="[876,964,1299,1326]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="219.[151,250,1846,1871]" captionTargetBox="[160,1423,191,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@219.[151,1436,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="219" captionText="FIGURE 86. Rhodesaclerda insleyae Hodgson &amp; Millar. Macropterous male. (Aclerdidae, Rhodesaclerdinae).Where D=simple pore and R=dermal reticulations on ocular sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3774350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3774350/files/figure.png" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852FB0FA9AFBE9D269" bold="true" box="[987,1058,1300,1326]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Body:</emphasis>
small to moderate in size; body with few setae, 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852D2DFAB6FC9AD215" box="[326,849,1336,1362]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">mostly on venter where mainly fleshy setae (fs)</emphasis>
; fs generally easy to differentiate from hair-like (hs) setae. Body often with fairly frequent small convex pores (cp) dorsally on thorax and/or abdomen. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852891FAD2FAF1D231" bold="true" box="[1274,1338,1372,1398]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Head</emphasis>
: median crest (mc) represented by slightly sclerotised ridge with a few striations. Dorsal mid-cranial ridge generally absent; ventral mid-cranial ridge (vmcr) very short to quite long, with hs ventral median ridge setae (vmcrs) posterior to each scape. Genae (g) unsclerotised, without polygonal reticulations; genal setae (gs) absent (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF8468528A0FA46FAB9D2A5" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[1227,1394,1480,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF8468528A0FA46FAB9D2A5" box="[1227,1394,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Rhodesaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or present (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852C90FA62FE6FD141" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[251,420,1516,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Kwazulaclerda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852C90FA62FE6FD141" box="[251,420,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Kwazulaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Eyes: two pairs of simple eyes, subequal in size. Ocelli (o) present and 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852893FA62FDE0D16D" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">surrounded by strong ridges from postocular ridge</emphasis>
. Ocular sclerite (ocs) sclerotised, 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852FC5F99EFAE9D16D" box="[942,1314,1552,1578]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">with some polygonal reticulation</emphasis>
. Preocular ridge very short (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852D0EF9BAFDC7D109" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[357,524,1588,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852D0EF9BAFDC7D109" box="[357,524,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Rhodesaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or absent (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852EF4F9BAFC83D109" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[671,840,1588,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Kwazulaclerda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852EF4F9BAFC83D109" box="[671,840,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Kwazulaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852F09F9BAFEB3D135" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Postocular ridge (procr) well developed. Postoccipital ridge absent</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852DE1F9D9FE36D135" bold="true" box="[394,509,1623,1650]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Antennae</emphasis>
: short, 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852E32F9D6FD2DD135" box="[601,742,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">7-segmented</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852E91F9D6FC6AD135" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[762,929,1624,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852E91F9D6FC6AD135" box="[762,929,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Rhodesaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852FBCF9D6FBADD135" box="[983,1126,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">8 segmented</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852811F9D6FAE8D135" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[1146,1315,1624,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Kwazulaclerda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852811F9D6FAE8D135" box="[1146,1315,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Kwazulaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), filiform; flagellar segments rather narrow, with short fs and an occasional hs; 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852FF1F9F2FEFCD1FD" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">bristles on subapical segments not apparently differentiated;</emphasis>
capitate setae present on apical segment. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852F7FF92EFC45D1FD" bold="true" box="[788,910,1696,1722]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Prothorax</emphasis>
: small convex pores (cp) present or absent on dorsum. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852C92F94AFE43D199" bold="true" box="[249,392,1732,1758]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Mesothorax</emphasis>
: scutum (sct): median membranous area small, about twice as wide as long; with 1 or 2 pairs hs scutal setae (scts). Scutellum (scl) rectangular, sclerotised and tubular, with a foramen; scutellar setae (scls) absent. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852CFCF882FDAFD061" box="[151,612,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Area within mesopostnotum unsclerotised</emphasis>
. Basisternum (stn 
<subScript id="179F59370AF846852F46F893FCFED06C" attach="left" box="[813,821,1821,1835]" fontSize="6" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">2</subScript>
) with well-developed median ridge (mdr) or represent- ed by weak sclerotisations; without basisternal setae (present on precoxal ridges of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF84685282AF8BEFB3AD00D" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[1089,1265,1840,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="combreticola">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF84685282AF8BEFB3AD00D" box="[1089,1265,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">R. combreticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lateropleurite (lpl) either very large, often extending anteriorly as well as laterally (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852FC4F8DAFB99D029" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[943,1106,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852FC4F8DAFB99D029" box="[943,1106,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Rhodesaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or narrow (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF84685288CF8DAFA47D029" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[1255,1420,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Kwazulaclerda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF84685288CF8DAFA47D029" box="[1255,1420,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Kwazulaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Mesothoracic spiracle (sp 
<subScript id="179F59370AF846852DDAF807FE72D0D0" attach="right" box="[433,441,1929,1943]" fontSize="6" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">2</subScript>
) 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852DA2F8F6FD58D0D5" box="[457,659,1912,1938]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">without disc-pores</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852ECAF8F6FBD9D0D5" box="[673,1042,1912,1938]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Postmesospiracular setae absent.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852873F8F6FB67D0D5" bold="true" box="[1048,1196,1912,1938]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Metathorax:</emphasis>
metathoracic spiracle (sp 
<subScript id="179F59370AF846852CD2F823FF0AD0FC" attach="right" box="[185,193,1965,1979]" fontSize="6" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">3</subScript>
) not placed more posteriorly than on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF846852E05F812FD12D0F1" box="[622,729,1948,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Coccidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852E8CF812FC72D0F1" box="[743,953,1948,1974]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">without disc-pores</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852FA2F812FE48D09E" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Anterior and posterior metasternal setae (amss, pmss) present</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852DF9F831FE15D09D" bold="true" box="[402,478,1983,2010]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Wings</emphasis>
: hyaline; narrow. Without alar lobes or alar setae. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852874F84EFA86D09D" box="[1055,1357,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Hamulohalteres (h) absent</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF846852937F84EFA5FD09D" bold="true" box="[1372,1428,1984,2010]" pageId="215" pageNumber="216">Legs</emphasis>
: with few setae, usually all hs or spur-like; often with radial ridges. Trochanter (tr) each with a longer seta ventrally. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2CFCFF33FDCAD790" box="[151,513,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Tarsal campaniform pore absent</emphasis>
. Claws (c) rather elongate and narrow, 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2FDEFF33FB92D790" box="[949,1113,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">with a denticle</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B280EFF32FB11D790" bold="true" box="[1125,1242,188,215]" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Abdomen</emphasis>
: segments I–VII: sternites (as) and tergites (at) all with sclerites; pleurites on segments IV–VII generally showing varying degrees of sclerotisation. Caudal extension (ce) of segment VII poorly developed or absent. Dorsal abdominal setae (ads) few, mainly hs; pleural setae (dps and vps) all hs on anterior segments, 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2FA7FEA7FAF6D604" box="[972,1341,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">fs present on posterior segments</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2926FEA7FC95D620" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">ventral abdominal setae (avs) abundant and fs on most or all sternites</emphasis>
. Small convex pores (cp) present on dorsum. Segment VIII: 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2D7CFEFFFC4CD6CC" box="[279,903,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">caudal extension present and lightly to well sclerotised</emphasis>
, each with 1 or 2 short hs; sternite (as) sclerotised, forming anterior section of penial sheath; without setae (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF6468B2F26FE1BFC3FD6E8" authorityName="McConnell" authorityYear="1954" box="[845,1012,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Rhodesaclerda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2F26FE1BFC3FD6E8" box="[845,1012,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Rhodesaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or with a pair of hs (
<taxonomicName id="4C1B20F10AF6468B2888FE1BFA47D6E8" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Millar" authorityYear="2002" box="[1251,1420,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Aclerdidae" genus="Kwazulaclerda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="217" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2888FE1BFA47D6E8" box="[1251,1420,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Kwazulaclerda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2CFCFE37FE30D694" box="[151,507,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Glandular pouches (gp) absent</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96F87600AF6468B2E60FE36FD11D694" bold="true" box="[523,730,440,467]" pageId="217" pageNumber="218">Genital segments</emphasis>
: penial sheath (ps) elongate; segment IX broad, narrowing to a blunt, rather parallel-sided, narrow style. Aedeagus (aed) quite long and broad; approximately parallel-sided or broadening slightly at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
